								</div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A1 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a1">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">Where can I Create my own comic and customized iBee™ Character?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">You can access the game on honeydefender.com by clicking on the “Create Your Own Comic” Feature then navigating to the “Create a Comic” or “iBee™” screen through the program home page or through the navigation bar at the top of your screen.<br />Remember, you’re going to need a code from a specially marked box of Honey Nut Cheerios to unlock all the available tools and assets within the program. 
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A2 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a2">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">Do I really need a code to unlock the assets with little gold locks next to them in the Create a Comic and iBee Libraries?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">Yes, you do. Look for specially marked boxes of Honey Nut Cheerios to find a code on the back of the box. The only box that will have the code looks like this on the front:<br />
                                    <div style="margin:0 auto 0 auto; text-align: center"><img src="assets/images/faq/faq_a2_box.png" width="177" height="200"></div><br />
                                    If you do not have a code you can still create super cool comics and iBee™ characters, but in order to use ALL the available assets within the Create a Comic and iBee™ libraries, you will need the code.
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A3 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a3">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">Will the program remember my code, or do I have to enter it every time?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">If your pop-up blockers are disabled, the game will remember your code and you shouldn’t have to enter it every time.
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A4 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a4">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">What happens if I enter a wrong code?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">The site will tell you that you have entered an incorrect code. Check your package and try again.
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A5 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a5">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">How do I delete an image from my comic?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">All you do is drag the asset outside of the comic frame until you see a red circle with a line through the asset.  Once the asset you wish to delete from your comic is outside the comic frame, it will discard once you release the mouse. 
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A6 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a6">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">What if I don’ t like my comic and want to start over?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">All you have to do is click “Start Over” and you will be asked to select a new Comic Strip layout, Story Starter and Title.<br />Remember, once you click “Start Over” you will not be able to re-access your last comic. 
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A7 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a7">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">How do I add dialog to the comic?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">Drag a dialog bubble into the frame you would like to add dialog to.  Click in the dialog bubble for all the fun and exciting phrases you can piece together to make your story!
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A8 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a8">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">How do I Save my comic?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">Once you are completely finished with your comic, simply click, I’m Done.  You will be asked if you would like to publish your comic to the comic gallery, and you need to click YES.  Once you click YES, you will receive a comic ID number and your comic will be published to the Comic Gallery.<br />Remember, if you want to find your comic, you need to search for your comic using the id number.
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A9 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a9">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">How do I become Hot Comic of the Week?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">If you’re comic received the highest number of “Likes” during the week prior, your comic will be featured as the hot comic of the week.  “Like” your comic and other people’s comics by clicking on the thumbnail comic image in the gallery, then clicking the “Like” button in the upper right hand corner. 
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A10 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a10">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">How do I Save my iBee™?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">Once you are completely finished with your iBee™, simply click, I’m Done.  You will first need to NAME your iBee™ using the drop down menu’s provided.  When finished, click OK and you will receive an iBee™ ID.  Be sure to write down your  iBee™ ID  so you can search for your iBee™ in iBee™ Nation. 
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A11 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a11">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">How do I add my iBee™ to my comic?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">After you’ve received an iBee™ ID, you should click the “Add to Comic” button and you will be taken to the Create a Comic screen where your iBee™ has been added to your Character library.  To access the Character Library, click on the 4th button from the top on the right side of your screen. 
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A12 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a12">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">How do I add other people’s iBees™ from iBee™ Nation to my comic?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">You will need to unlock this functionality by using the code on the back of specially marked boxes of Honey Nut Cheerios Cereal boxes.  Go to the “Unlock Bonus Stuff” navigation, enter in the code, and you can include any iBee™ in iBee™ Nation into the comics you create. 
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <!-- FAQ A13 -->
                                
                                <div class="faq_content_answer" id="faq_a13">
                                	<div class="faq_content_answer_title">Do I have to call you every time I have a question?</div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_text">No, most of your questions can be answered either in the Help section on the site or through the “helpful hints” section at the bottom of the Create a Comic screen.
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="faq_content_answer_back"><a href="#topnav">- BACK TO TOP -</a></div>
                                </div>
							</td> 
